truth: It was the same shop, same items as always. What was weird... was one of us.
iris: O-one of us?..
truth: The person who was acting weird was:
- Me
- Iris
- Mark
- Kevin
truth: Something about Kevin... he wasn't acting like himself that day. He kept doing little things that didn't make sense.
kevin: Me? Do tell, what did I do that was soooooo weird? 
truth: The evidence that points to his weird behavior is: *Option to select piece of evidence, present Mark's account*
truth: The two of you always, without fail, go to the tabletop section of the store. But this time, Kevin went to the complete opposite side.
kevin: ... Really? I'm so weird for *that*? God forbid a man wants to check out a new spot..
iris: U-um, can I also say something?
mark: You don't need to ask permission. Speak your mind.
iris: Thanks... I just wanted to say, he also acted weird... he kept looking around and going to the b-boring areas.
truth: Looking around?
iris: Y-yea looking around! His h-head was on a spinner.
truth: Head on a swivel, Iris... 
kevin: I actually can't believe we're all here to talk about this. 
kevin: I learned to stop restricting myself and try new things. You should too... you never know what might become visible if you actually look.